    'history.tag': 'Department history',
    'history.title': 'From the origins to <em>the present day</em>',
    'history.h1Title': 'Department Founded',
    'history.h1Text': 'The Department of Spirit Technology was founded in 1930 as part of the Kyiv Institute of National Economy. Its founders were A.A. Fuks, I.P. Vavilov, A.L. Malchenko, and I.H. Hrytsyuk.',
    'history.h1Detail': 'Later the All-Union Institute of the Spirit Industry was established, with the Department of Spirit Technology as its core. In 1933 this institute merged with the Kyiv Technological Institute of Sugar. The Kyiv Spirit-Fermentation Institute and the Kyiv Fermentation Institute subsequently joined. In 1935 the present-day NUFT was named the Kyiv Technological Institute of the Food Industry, and the department was renamed to "Fermentation Technology". The first head of the department until World War II was Professor A.A. Fuks. Distinguished scientists who shaped the department included Prof. O.O. Kirov, and Assoc. Profs. A.L. Malchenko, I.P. Vavilov, I.M. Roiter, M.M. Khrystenko, and A.H. Zabrodskyi.',
    'history.h2Title': 'War Years and Recovery',
    'history.h2Text': 'With the onset of war, some staff were called up to the army, others were evacuated. After the liberation of Kyiv, the department resumed work under Prof. P.M. Maltsev.',
    'history.h2Detail': 'Y.L. Safris, I.M. Roiter, L.Y. Yasinskyi, M.M. Khrystenko, and Y.M. Kulinovskyi were called up. I.L. Safris and L.Y. Yasinskyi perished. O.O. Kirov, V.I. Lanovyi, and I.H. Teplytskyi remained in occupied Kyiv. A.A. Fuks, I.H. Hrytsyuk, A.H. Zabrodskyi, I.P. Vavilov, P.M. Maltsev, and M.M. Korobov were evacuated and worked in the spirit and brewing industries. After liberation, the department resumed operations and was headed by Prof. P.M. Maltsev, Doctor of Technical Sciences, Honoured Education Worker of Ukraine, until 1972. The department staff included Assoc. Profs. O.I. Oleinikova, M.M. Korobov, M.M. Khrystenko, and I.M. Roiter.',
    'history.h3Title': 'Post-War Growth',
    'history.h3Text': 'As the number of students grew, the department\'s teaching workload expanded. Postgraduate admissions resumed and the staff was reinforced with new associate professors.',
    'history.h3Detail': 'The teaching staff was joined by Assoc. Profs. B.D. Metiushov, M.V. Zazirna, Ye.I. Velyka, V.K. Tomashevych, V.Kh. Sukhodol, and V.O. Marynchenko. Later the department expanded with KTIFP graduates who completed postgraduate studies and defended their dissertations — V.M. Shvets, N.O. Yemelianova, P.V. Kolotusha, A.Ye. Meletiev, O.M. Protsenko, N.Ya. Hrechko, A.M. Kuts, P.L. Shyian, P.I. Meniailo, H.H. Drozdova, and others.',
    'history.h4Title': 'Professor P.S. Tsyhankov',
    'history.h4Text': 'In 1973–1978 the department was headed by Prof. P.S. Tsyhankov, a distinguished specialist in spirit rectification.',
    'history.h4Detail': 'Professor Tsyhankov was a scholar with extensive teaching experience. He authored over 170 scientific works and 40 patents, including monographs, textbooks, and manuals. Under his leadership, innovative distillation equipment was developed and manufactured in Ukraine for the spirit industry.',
    'history.h5Title': 'Professor V.A. Domaretskyi',
    'history.h5Text': 'For over 25 years (1979–2005) the department was headed by Professor V.A. Domaretskyi, Doctor of Technical Sciences, Honoured Education Worker of Ukraine.',
    'history.h5Detail': 'During this period the department\'s staff included Profs. V.O. Marynchenko, A.Ye. Meletiev, P.L. Shyian, O.S. Lukanin, L.S. Dehtiarov, and Assoc. Profs. A.M. Kuts, S.R. Todosiichuk, N.Ya. Hrechko, H.H. Drozdova, V.M. Koshova, V.L. Prybylskyi, M.V. Karputina, M.M. Kovalov, V.M. Sydor, A.M. Fishchenko, N.E. Frolova, M.V. Bilko, Z.M. Romanova, and O.P. Vitriak. In 1992 the department began training specialists in winemaking technology, and in 1997 the first class of wine engineer-technologists graduated.',
    'history.h6Title': 'Professor P.L. Shyian',
    'history.h6Text': 'From 2005 to 2018 the department was headed by Professor P.L. Shyian, Doctor of Technical Sciences, laureate of the State Prize of Ukraine, and Honoured Inventor of Ukraine.',
    'history.h6Detail': 'Prof. Shyian rose from a senior engineer at the Institute of Microbiology of the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine to Dean of the Faculty of Fermentation, Canning, and Sugar Production at NUFT. He was a laureate of the State Prize of Ukraine in Science and Technology (1998), Honoured Inventor of Ukraine, and winner of the All-Ukrainian "Inventor of the Year" competition.',
    'history.h7Title': 'Present Day — Assoc. Prof. A.M. Kuts',
    'history.h7Text': 'The department is currently headed by Assoc. Prof. A.M. Kuts, Candidate of Technical Sciences. The department is developing dynamically, introducing dual education and international programmes.',
    'history.h7Detail': 'The department\'s staff includes Profs. M.V. Bilko and V.L. Prybylskyi (Doctors of Technical Sciences), and Assoc. Profs. I.M. Babych, P.M. Boiko, M.V. Bondar, Yu.V. Bulii, R.M. Mukoid, and Z.M. Romanova. Head of Department A.M. Kuts is an expert of the State Accreditation Commission in "Food Technologies and Engineering". Prof. Bilko chairs the Specialized Academic Council 05.18.07 and is a member of the Technical Committee of the Wine Industry. Since 1931 the department has trained approximately 7,000 specialists in the fermentation field. The department graduates about 35 bachelors and masters annually.',
